    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends 👋, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change padding of mui badge in react js, you can put . it will change padding of mui badge in React JS. Today, I am…","html":"<p>Hi Friends 👋,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change padding of mui badge in react js, you can put <code class=\"language-text\">padding: \"20px\"</code>. it will change padding of mui badge in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change padding of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui Badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI badge.</li>\n<li>Use the badge Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI badge.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> makeStyles <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/styles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the badge Component</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">badge</code> component in your react js. For example, The badge component is used notifications to users. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Badge></code> component make a badge in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"secondary\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Your content */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change padding of mui badge example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, The <code class=\"language-text\">badgeContainer</code> class comes from the <code class=\"language-text\">makeStyles</code> function and is used to apply the defined styles to the <code class=\"language-text\">container</code>.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> makeStyles <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/styles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> useStyles <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">makeStyles</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">theme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">badgeContainer</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">padding</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"20px\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Adjust the padding as per your requirements</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">MyComponent</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> classes <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useStyles</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>classes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>badgeContainer<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Badge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> color<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"secondary\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Your content */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Badge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> MyComponent<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and changed padding of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 309px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/73db6181345361f3aa59d34ca1c32374/451be/padding-of-mui-badge.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 48.734177215189874%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlAAAABXRUJQVlA4IEQAAABwAwCdASoUAAoAPtFWpUwoJKOiMAgBABoJQBOgBDv5wvBreggA+p/t6WlaA5BFkG9PZHseQC5lp1QIktJdTDzZ7xcAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, padding, badge\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, padding, badge\"\n        src=\"/static/73db6181345361f3aa59d34ca1c32374/451be/padding-of-mui-badge.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/73db6181345361f3aa59d34ca1c32374/81b7c/padding-of-mui-badge.webp 158w,\n/static/73db6181345361f3aa59d34ca1c32374/451be/padding-of-mui-badge.webp 309w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 309px) 100vw, 309px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change padding of mui badge in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=modest-jones-z6z8lv\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best 👍</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to change padding of mui badge in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"July 03, 2023","description":"Example of change padding of mui badge in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui badge with tooltip in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-04-how-to-show-mui-badge-with-tooltip-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to show mui badge with icon in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-03-how-to-show-mui-badge-with-icon-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-07-03-how-to-change-padding-of-mui-badge-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-07-04-how-to-show-mui-badge-with-tooltip-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-07-03-how-to-show-mui-badge-with-icon-in-react-js/"}},
